orrect myself—the second session's start time converts to 17:43 UTC, not 18:15 as I initially thought, so the duration is actually 2 hours 47 minutes, not 56 minutes.\n\nFor the QLHV group session, I'm calculating that it's been running for about 9 hours 48 minutes since it started at 15:03 UTC, but I should double-check this calculation.\n\nLet me recalculate the time difference more carefully: from 15:03 to 20:31 is 5 hours and 28 minutes, which gives me roughly 9 hours 49 minutes when I account for the full duration. Now I'm compiling the session data and preparing to send the report to Lead via Telegram, including the four active sessions with their statuses and runtimes.\n\nI'm also double-checking the session list against the complete data—verifying which sessions are still running versus which have ended, and noting that the cron sessions are still active while some of the subagent sessions have finished or been killed. I'm noticing the DTLX group session ended at 17:15 UTC, which is earlier than I initially thought, so that's not an active concern. Now I need to verify the cron:e7885813 session status more carefully—checking whether it's running or done by looking at the systemSent and updatedAt timestamps from the session data. Let me verify the math on this - from 17:17 UTC to 20:31 UTC is about 3 hours and 14 minutes, which matches my calculation of roughly 3h14m. So cron:e7885813 is the Agent Status to Lead cron session that's been running for about 3h14m.\n\nNow I'm compiling the final status report with all the active sessions and their durations."},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll compile the report from the live session data and send it to Lead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n03qcyfa86a2_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 20:31 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 4\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p Monitor): running — Monitoring DTLX ecosystem p